The paper deals with the development of deep neural networks for the segmentation of retinal layers from OCT images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of machine learning methods such as pixel-wise labeling and regression networks also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of simulated masks for training the R-Net, which could fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
